  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Response to Floods in Niger</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">2010 floods have affected 300,000 persons in differents regions of Niger, including Niamey. The project aims to  mitigate the critical food insecurity and health risks of 28,000 vulnerable persons affected by the floods through voucher for food access and livelihoods recovery, water, sanitation and public health promotion. The project falls under SCO 1.1 &amp; 3.1.</narrative>
  </description>
